  "doc_id": "7830",
  "text": "In addition to the deicing robot walking mechanism, the working head part is one of the key technologies of the deicing operation success or failure. However, in the variety of deicing robots, the work head works mostly following the early method of using blade scraping and knock [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This is not conducive to the stable and the efficient implementation in the span flexible wire environment; what is more worth mentioning is that blade scraping and knock are easy to damage the line. After viewing the above problem, this paper proposes a local incentive displacement deicing method, which can be implemented by the working head of the deicing robot. That is, to constrain a length of iced wire, using eccentric vibrator to produce an incentive displacement to form a local vibration, the alternating stress and displacement are generated, to make ice break off from the wire, so as to realize the deicing of the icing line. In this case, the alternating displacement of the wire will be controlled by the eccentricity, which can ensure the stability of deicing operation.",
  "correct_citation": {
